com.seagullsw.appinterface.client

Class BasicAppInterfaceConnection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.seagullsw.appinterface.client.BasicAppInterfaceConnection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AppInterfaceConnection
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CicsEngineAppInterfaceConnection, TextAppInterfaceConnection

    public abstract class BasicAppInterfaceConnection
extends java.lang.Object
implements AppInterfaceConnection
    This base abstract class may be extended to accommodate a variety of client-server communication protocols, such as sockets or HTTP.
    See Also:
    SocketAppInterfaceConnection, TODO: Add IO WP

      • execute

        public com.seagullsw.appinterface.model.data.Response execute(com.seagullsw.appinterface.model.data.Request request)
                                                       throws java.io.IOException

        Sends a Request object to the back-end for execution, and returns a Response object.

        If the connection has not explicitly been opened with open(), then it will automatically be opened, the request executed in a separate session, and finally the connection closed. Alternatively, the connection may first be opened explicitly, after which all subsequent invocations of execute() will be processed in the same session until the connection is explicitly closed with close(). In this regard, see also AppInterfaceCommand.execute().

        NOTE: This method is not currently intended for general use by clients.

        Specified by:
        execute in interface AppInterfaceConnection
        Parameters:
        request - The Request to execute.
        Returns:
        The execute Response
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • execute

        public abstract java.lang.String execute(java.lang.String request)
                                  throws java.io.IOException

        String-oriented variant of the execute(Request) method. Accepts requests and returns responses encoded in the XML runtime data syntax specified in the chapter "XML Interfaces of the Application Interface Server" of the "Application Interface Programming Reference Manual."

        If the connection has not explicitly been opened with open(), then it will automatically be opened, the request executed in a separate session, and finally the connection closed. Alternatively, the connection may first be opened explicitly, after which all subsequent invocations of execute() will be processed in the same session until the connection is explicitly closed with close(). In this regard, see also AppInterfaceCommand.execute().

        Specified by:
        execute in interface AppInterfaceConnection
        Parameters:
        request -
        Returns:
        String
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
